response: "{ \"title\": \"Maximum Area of Isogram\", \"description\": \"An isogram is a word or phrase without a specific letter appearing more than once. Write a function `max_isogram_area` that takes a string as an input and returns the maximum area of any rectangle with its sides parallel to the axes that can be inscribed within the grid created by the letters in the string.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef max_isogram_area(s: str) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s` (str): A string containing lowercase English letters and/or spaces.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the maximum area of any rectangle that can be inscribed within the grid created by the letters in the input string.\\n\", \"code\": \"def max_isogram_area(s: str) -> int:\\n    if not s:\\n        return 0\\n    width = len(s)\\n    height = set(s.replace(' ', ''))\\n    return width * height\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert max_isogram_area(\\\"a\\\") == 1\", \"assert max_isogram_area(\\\"ab\\\") == 2\", \"assert max_isogram_area(\\\"abc\\\") == 3\", \"assert max_isogram_area(\\\"abcdefg\\\") == 7\"] }"
